metadata.title: 08_EVIDENCE_AND_CONFIDENCE - Classification Confidence Analysis
metadata.format: Consolidated evidence and confidence metrics without full function list

high_confidence_functions.description: Sample of high confidence functions across modules

low_confidence_functions.description: Sample of low confidence functions primarily in unknown module

examples: stdlib function signatures (compared to known APIs)
Functions with unique identifying strings + correct call patterns
Modules with high cohesion + clear boundaries
Algorithms with characteristic patterns (graph coloring signs)

MEDIUM.definition: Single strong evidence source or multiple weak sources

examples: Functions classified only by module proximity
Algorithm guesses based on size alone

string_references.strength: HIGH when unique, MEDIUM when common
string_references.limitations: Only 3-4% of functions have useful strings

decompilation.limitations: Time-intensive, only done for critical functions
